Language: Ilocano
Language code: ilo
Lines: orth orth-seg gloss translat
Author: James Blackburn, Kazuki Shintani
Date: April 7, 2016
Source a: Rubino, Carl. Reference grammar of Ilocano. Diss. University of California, Santa Barbara, 1997.



# Ex.1: grammatically correct VS order with intransitive verb
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Naglaylay ti sabong
n-ag-laylay ti sabong
PF-1-wilt ART flower.ABS
`The flower wilted'

# Ex.2: grammatically incorrect VS order with intransitive verb
Source: a:187
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Ti sabong naglaylay
ti sabong n-ag-laylay
ART flower.ABS PF-1-wilt 
`The flower wilted'

# Ex. 3: Incorrect use of verbal arguments/transitivity.
Source: a:?
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {c}
Nagtudo iti balay
n-ag-tudo    iti    balay
PF-I-rain    OBL    house
'It rained the house'

# Ex. 4: correct article-to-noun order
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wo}
Naglaylay ti sabong
n-ag-laylay ti sabong
PF-1-wilt ART flower.ABS
`The flower wilted'

# Ex. 5: incorrect article-to-noun order
Source: a:187
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
Naglaylay sabong ti
n-ag-laylay sabong ti
PF-1-wilt flower.ABS ART
`The flower wilted'

# Ex. 6: correct singular determiner
Source: a:194
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {det}
Nagsangit ti lalaki
n-ag-sangit ti lalaki
PF-I-cry ART boy
`The boy cried'

# Ex. 7: correct plural determiner
Source: a:194
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {det}
Nagsangit dagiti lalaki
n-ag-sangit dagiti lalaki
PF-I-cry PL boy
`The boys cried'

# Ex. 8: incorrect plural determiner case
Source: a:194
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {c}
Nagsangit dagiti lalaki
n-ag-sangit dagiti lalaki
PF-I-cry OBL.PL boy
`The boys cried'

# Ex. 9: incorrect word order with transitive verb: tr core-NP missing
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
Nakita ti babai
nakita ART babai
saw the girl
`The girl saw'

# Ex. 10: correct word order with transitive verb: tr core-NP core-NP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wo}
Nakita ti babai ti lalaki
nakita ART babai ART lalaki
saw the girl the boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# Ex. 11: incorrect word order with transitive verb: core-NP tr core-NP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
Ti babai nakita ti lalaki
ART babai nakita ART lalaki
the girl saw the boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# Ex. 12: incorrect word order with transitive verb: core-NP core-NP tr
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
Ti babai ti lalaki nakita
ART babai ART lalaki nakita
the girl the boy saw
`The girl saw the boy'

# Ex. 13: incorrect NP case with transitive verb: tr oblique-NP oblique-NP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {c}
Nakita iti babai iti lalaki
nakita OBL babai OBL lalaki
saw the girl the boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# Ex. 14: incorrect word order and case with transitive verb: oblique-NP tr oblique-NP
Source: a:32
Vetted: s
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wo}
Iti babai nakita iti lalaki
OBL babai nakita OBL lalaki
the girl saw the boy
`The girl saw the boy'

# Ex. 15: incorrect word order with transitive verb: oblique-NP oblique-NP tr
